content.description: Stand start with left hand edge and right hand sidepull. Climb the intimidating face.
content.protection: 2+ pads. Good landing, just very tall.
content.location: The first tall face seen from the railroad tracks

content.description: SDS matched on good edge. Climb a series of crimps into the same topout as Vantablack.
content.protection: 2+ pads. Good landing, just very tall.
content.location: Left of Vantablack, on the same wall.

content.description: SDS on sidepull rail. Hit a small slopey rail and bust right to a good hold.
content.location: Up and right of Menhir and Bone & Amber. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down the talus to the left.

content.description: SDS on jug and climb straight up through an awesome sloper. The sloper stays wet for a while after rain.
content.location: Up and left of Menhir and Bone & Amber. Hidden in the trees. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down to the right through an overgrown ramp.

content.description: SDS on large edge. Climb several crimps to the refrigerator compression feature.
content.location: Left of terraform, on the same wall. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down to the right through an overgrown ramp. Hidden in the trees.

content.description:
Stand start on large block and do several powerful moves up the short bulge. 

 *Only accessible in the winter, when the water is frozen*
content.location: Base of the quarry. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down the talus to the left.

content.description: Stand start compressing arete below the break. Climb the cool feature.
content.location: Above and left of Bone & Amber. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down the talus to the left.

content.description: Start on top of the pedestal in the corner. Step out over the abyss and climb the tall slab.
content.protection: 4+ pads. The landing is tiered and heavily slanted. Hard to protect.
content.location: The tall slab to the right of the vantablack face (the first tall face seen from the tracks.)

content.description: SDS on obvious rail/undercling. Climb the narrow compression feature.
content.location: The first boulder off the tracks; hidden in the trees a bit. If you see the Vantablack face, you've gone too far.

content.description: Stand start with left hand on arete, right hand on lower jug edge. Climb directly up the tricky arete.
content.location: At the base of the main quarry. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down the talus to the left.

content.description: Start on obvious crimps and climb overhanging face, likely using a jug up and right.
content.location: To the right of Bone & Amber at the base of the quarry. From the tracks, follow the social trail to the top of the dome and follow it straight back to the overlook. Cut down the talus to the left.

content.description: The larger of the two quarries. It contains the highest concentration of boulders in the park. The standout here is the Vantablack, one of the best boulders you'll find in the state. There are several problems that can only be climbed in the winter, when the water is frozen.
